Since 2012, Sunnaas Hospital has been using video conferences to provide multidisciplinary follow-up for people with spinal cord injuries and pressure sores, in close
collaboration with the home nursing service in the municipality. A cost-benefit evaluation of this patient group showed that video consultations cost 15 per cent of what
physical meetings in outpatient clinics would cost, and only 3 percent of the costs
