Home dialysis with digital monitoring
Getting treatment at home instead of travelling to hospital several times a week gives
patients more freedom. Nordland Hospital Trust has been working with ­Telenor on a
solution to improve how patients using home dialysis are monitored. Patients record
their measurements on an app on their mobile, while weight and blood pressure are
recorded automatically. The kidney nurse at the hospital gets a faster picture of
the patient’s condition than when data has to be collected and registered manually.
Another benefit is that the medical personnel can be better prepared when they see
patients – whether that is over the phone or in person.
